GA4GH Variation Representation — JSON Schema Model
All classes have a string `type`.
Dashed lines denote abstract classes. Abstract classes are not instantiated.
Thin solid lines denote classes that may be instantiated but are not identifiable.
Bold lines denote identifiable objects (i.e., may be serialized ad identified by computed identifier).
Solid arrow lines denoted inheritance. Subclasses inherit all attributes from their parent. Inherited attributes are not shown.
